Collaboration: Development and operation teams collaborate in a functional team that works together throughout the development and deployment process.
Automation: Automation is key in software development, this dives developers more time to write code and develop new features. It also reduces human error and allows teams to achieve continuous improvement while quickly respoding to customer feedback.
Continuous Improvement: This is the practice of focusing on experimentation, minimizing waste, and optimizing for speed, cost, and ease of delivery. Which allows DevOps teams to continuously push updates to improve efficiency.
Customer-Centric Action: DevOps teams use short feedback loops with customers and end users to develop products and services centered around users needs.
Create with the End in Mind: This principle is understanding the needs of customers and creating products to solve real world problems.
